President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2 through May 8, 2010, as National Charter Schools Week in the United States. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of education and how charter schools serve as laboratories for innovative teaching and learning methods. The President highlights the role of charter schools in unlocking the potential of students from all backgrounds and driving education reform. He calls on communities and states to support charter schools and ensure that all students have access to a high-quality education. The proclamation emphasizes the need for creative teaching strategies and learning techniques to prepare the next generation of leaders. Ultimately, President Obama believes that a world-class education is crucial for the prosperity of the country and empowering young Americans to achieve their dreams.